        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10131.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from F. J. Cohn, 21 August 1875</ref>, in which Cohn discussed <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In his letter of 21 August 1875, Cohn had queried whether CD had shown that the substance aggregated in cells of the tentacles of <hi rend="italic">Drosera rotundifolia</hi> (common or round-leaved sundew) was protoplasm. In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref>, p. 38, CD described colourless circulating protoplasm lining the cell walls with a homogeneous purple fluid in the centre.</note>
